<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-588-373  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 588 373.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC Professional  May 1989 v8 n5 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Your Vista to VAX data: CDC's Vista Application Link providestransparent access to VAX data. (Control DataCorporation)(connecting microcomputers to VAXs) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, David B.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Control Data Corporation's Vista Applications Link allows users ofLotus 1-2-3, dBase and Symphony to transparently access datastored on DEC VAXs without rekeying.andP;  Users never leave the Lotus1-2-3, Symphony or dBase environments, which eliminates the needto learn a new application.andP;  Priced from $2,000 to $40,000,depending on system configuration, Vista Applications Linkoperates on IBM PC, XT, AT and PS-2 computers and compatibles andcan access VAX systems running VMS or ULTRIX.andP;  Three componentsmake up Vista Applications Link.andP;  A Lotus add-in program, LotusPC-T-A-C, provides the interface to the personal computer'sapplication software.andP;  VistaDBLINK and VistaTACLINK provide VAXand microcomputer interfaces and communications control.andO;Interfaces are available to access VAX databases such as Oracle,Informix, Unify, Ingres, IM-DM, DBMS and Rdb.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Control Data Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    CDA.andO;Product:   Vista Application Link (computer network software) (productintroduction)DEC VAX (Minicomputer) (computer programs)Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (equipment and supplies)dBASE (Data base management system) (equipment and supplies)Symphony (Integrated software) (equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     ConnectivityMicro-Minicomputer CommunicationData Base Management SystemsProduct Introduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Vista Application Link lets Lotus 1-2-3 and dBase users access VAXdata. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>